ABUJA – President of the Nigerian Labour Congress, Ayuba Wabba has admonished Muslims to use the occasion of the Eid-el- Kabir festivities to reflect on the Nigerian state and expose ways to make it greater. Wabba in his message to Nigerians, said sallah symbolises love through sharing, humility, peace and good neighbourliness. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Although public sector workers in Nigeria have been waiting on government across board to implement the National Minimum Wage of N30,000, the Labour leader said the Eid-el-Kabir festivities came at a time of great challenges, both economic and social, challenges that threaten our common bond and values that hold us together. His words, “We at the Nigeria Labour Congress wish to congratulate our Muslim faithful as they mark Eid-el-Kabir. “Eid-el-Kabir represents total and unquestioning obedience to Allah’s command and ultimate sacrifice. “It also symbolises love (through sharing), humility, peace and good neighbourliness. “We do believe this Eid-el- Kabir has come at a time of great challenges, both economic and social, challenges that threaten our common bond and values that hold us together. “It therefore offers us a great opportunity for deep reflection and rededication of our lives.”